name: Fernando Melek

deck: Turkish comic book artist, writer and cartoonist.
description:
His first cartoon was published in the magazine "Dogan Kardes" when he was in primary school. During his student time on the Istanbul State Academy of Fine Arts (now Mimar Sinan Fine Arts University) he made his first professional works. Sezgin Burak worked for many magazines as cartoonist. For the newspaper Cumhuriyet he illustrated the novels "Yilanlarin Öcü" by Fakir Baykurt and "Ince Memed" (Memed, My Hawk) and "Agri Dagi Efsanesi" by Yasar Kemal. 
 
In 1964 he created the comic strip "Bizimkiler". In 1966 he created Tarkan, his most famous comic character. 
In the 1960's he worked in Italy. In that time he penciled Kolosso and created the western character El Cougar. 
 
He commited suicide in 1978.
name: Sezgin Burak

deck: Artyom Gabrelyanov is Russian comic book editor and writer. He is editor-in-chief of Bubble.
name: Artyom Gabrelyanov

description:
Graduated school #716. Then he studied at the MARKHI (Moscow Institute of Architecture). After he worked as illustrator in magazines Pervoklashka and Self-defense without weapons (Sambo).

He also helped create the game Monopoly Online.
name: Vyacheslav Doronin

description:
Letterer and editor of Bubble comics.

Also guitarist and vocalist of post-punk band The Forced Oscillations (Вынужденные Колебания), also bass at Notchnoi Prospekt (Ночной Проспект), previously Zuboff Sex Shop, Vriemia Srat' (Время Срать) and more briefly. Music journalist, exploring Russian 80-90s underground scene. Has interest in Indo-Iranian and Balto-Slavic cultures and their intersections.
name: Sviatoslav Kaverin

description: Also he wrote many popular fantastic novels: Аномальные каникулы (S.T.A.L.K.E.R. Video Game Tie-In), В зоне тумана (S.T.A.L.K.E.R. Video Game Tie-In), Живое и мертвое, Живое и мертвое: Ученик мага, Зачистка, Земля — Паладос — Земля, Калинов мост, Мама, Гость внутри.

description: Also he wrote "Потревоженное проклятие", dilogy "Твой демон зла", series "Пастыри", "Марш мародеров" and many others. Volkov participated in the project "Этногенез".

description:
Main projects for 2017:

1. Metropolis. It is a comic in the noir style, inspired by "Sin City". Comics will be animated to dark and cruel game.

2. Cyrillic project. I have dream to create a new comics universe, where heroes of Slavic fairy tales lives in our world. For now I have only heroes, because I can work on it only in my free time.

3. Pestilence at AfterShock Comics, teaming with veteran comics writer Frank Tieri.
name: Oleg Okunev
